Introduction


We are interested in housing in King County because we all attend college in King County and consider it to be our home, even if just temporarily. Housing and homelessness are hot topics in Seattle right now and pressing issues. We’d all like to learn more about it, contribute our power to the community


We used this dataset to help us better understand housing in King Country: House Sales in King County USA. This data was collected by the King County Department of Housing and is hosted on a website called Kaggle. Its informations included such as specific living space in sqft, numbers of bedrooms and bathrooms are really specific. After analysing the dataset, we hope to find out:

  • How house prices have changed in King County?

  • What zip codes have the most/least number of sales?

  • What are the average square foot of house purchases?


Summary Info:

For the dataset, it has are 21 columns in this data frame. The average price of the homes sold are $5.40088110^{5}. The oldest house sold was built in 1900, and the newest was built in 2015. The average square footage above ground was 1788.4 ft.
